      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For meetings, stick to charcoal or navy suits with a crisp white or light blue shirt; ties should be silk with subtle patterns, and shoes must be polished leather Oxfords. In dining, always wait for the host to begin eating and use proper silverware etiquette, never reaching across the table. When communicating, adopt a measured, formal tone, avoiding slang or overly emotional language, as this signals a level of cultivated control.",
